@node WHAT_IS "What is UUCP2Fido"

        This  program  is  part  of  the  "Monalisa" project that
        consists  in  a  series of other programs that, together,
        can  perform  powerful  and  flexible  operations  within
        FidoNet  and other Networks.  Read Monalisa documentation
        for more details.

        UUCP2Fido  is  basicaly a message standard converter.  It
        will  convert  the articles from the Usenet Newsgroups to
        Fidonet Echomail areas.  You must use this is conjunction
        with Amiga-UUCP V1.16 or higher or any other UUCP package
        that  relies  on  bacth  files,  compressed  or  not,  in
        UUSPOOL:.
@endnode
@node HOW_DOES_IT_WORKS "How does it works"

        UUCP2Fido  will  scan your UUSPOOL:  directory and search
        for  batch files to a pre-specified system.  It will then
        decompress  those batches, convert the Usenet Articles to
        Fidonet  Messages  and  pack  them  to .PKTs in your Fido
        InBound  directory using @{"PKTGen" link "Monalisa:Documentation/Programs/PKTgen/main"}, another program from the
        Monalisa project.

        UUCP2Fido  is,  I  believe,  a  very fast converter as it
        works  with  big  files instead of undreds of small files
        (single  articles).   However, It doesn't spend that much
        memory   from  your  environment.   Instead,  it  may  be
        configured   to   use  the  disk  instead  of  RAM  (Work
        Directory).
@endnode
